{
  "stem": "4247.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At the time I wasn't fully aware of that, because I thought that, you know, being in Hungary, part of the Balkan or very close to it, we have an inferior education.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Far from it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think the curriculum, what we were taught, was excellent.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But most importantly, we have learned discipline, and we learned how to behave for the rest of our lives.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that was very valuable.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, discipline was ruling our home life as well, because obviously what we were taught in the school was in the atmosphere, in the atmosphere that was carried over in all aspects of life, including home life.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, my home life was essentially-- I-- I would not say that my home life was ruled by discipline.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a mixture of discipline and-- and-- and family love, which was an excellent mixture.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and-- you know, we-- in our family, we all knew where we stood, we know what-- what our individual rules and obligations were.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My obligation was to-- to get through my studies and make sure that I don't fail.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and my father was in a very modest financial circumstances.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had to pay a rather high tuition fee to the school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it would have been an issue of letting him down if I was-- had I been unable to cope with the issues.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was the only child.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Only my father, my mother, and myself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Very strangely, while our grandparents' family was always [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] marking a large family of seven, eight, nine children, the next generation, my mother's, my father's generation, usually had only one, or maximum, two children.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Look, I-- interesting question.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think the reason my grandparents had so many children was, I imagine, a religious issue primarily.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
